# Website FormTextField direction

Applies when editing shared text inputs under `website/src/app/ui/components/form/`. Authority: `docs/platforms/website/flow-form-foundation.md` §3.1.

## Rule

`FormTextField` (and wrappers that only re-export it) MUST inherit the document/page direction from the active locale.

- Use logical alignment: `textAlign: "start"` in `cssStyle`.
- Do **not** set Utils `ltr` or `ta_l` on the native `<input>` / `<textarea>`.

### Exception — optional `suffix`

When `suffix` is set, the **input + suffix** wrapper `Row` uses Utils `ltr` so the suffix stays on the **visual right** in both `ar` and `en` (e.g. org subdomain + `.ejtmaa.live`). The native input still does not force `ltr`/`ta_l` on its own outside that row.

## Why

Forcing `direction: ltr` + left align on an RTL page makes the caret appear stuck at the visual start when typing Arabic (and fights the product’s default `ar` locale). Host suffixes are machine LTR chrome and must remain right-aligned regardless of page locale.

## Forbidden

- Hardcoded `ltr` / `rtl` / `ta_l` / `ta_r` on shared form text fields “for email/password convenience” unless a future product decision documents a per-`type` exception in `flow-form-foundation.md`.
- Inventing a parallel text field component to work around direction instead of fixing `FormTextField`.
- Putting the host suffix only in `subTitle` / `actionArea` when the product requires it beside the input — use `suffix`.

